<subSubSection id="7C85650B6C66FF8DFF71F9BFFDA2F0E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="353" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="342036806C66FF8DFF71F9BFFCAAF069" blockId="0.[166,836,1570,1598]" box="[166,836,1570,1598]" pageId="0" pageNumber="353">
<heading id="6F6881EC6C66FF8DFF71F9BFFCAAF069" box="[166,836,1570,1598]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="0" pageNumber="353" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="F39F4D036C66FF8DFF71F9BFFE2EF06A" authorityName="Schiffermuller" authorityYear="1776" box="[166,448,1570,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="353" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacephala">
<emphasis id="06EBEA926C66FF8DFF71F9BFFE2EF06A" bold="true" box="[166,448,1570,1597]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="353">Acronicta megacephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
([Denis et Schiffermüller], 1775)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="342036806C66FF8DFF0CF9FFFDA2F0E9" blockId="0.[166,1225,1635,1854]" pageId="0" pageNumber="353">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Egg subspherical, flattened (
<figureCitation id="ACA42A056C66FF8DFD29F9FFFCD2F029" box="[766,828,1635,1662]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[172,205,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[174,1228,201,1672]" captionTargetId="figure-5@1.[174,1228,201,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Eggs of Acronictinae: Acronicta megacephala. Scale bars: 1, 4 — 100 µm; 2, 3, 5, 6 — 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453276/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="353">fig. 1</figureCitation>
), height 
<quantity id="F3679B656C66FF8DFC78F9FFFBA1F029" box="[943,1103,1635,1662]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="353" unit="mm" value="0.375" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.35">0.35–0.4 mm</quantity>
, diameter 
<quantity id="F3679B656C66FF8DFF71F91FFEDFF0C9" box="[166,305,1667,1694]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="0" pageNumber="353" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.2 mm</quantity>
(n = 2). Egg light green with purple spot at apical part and smaller spots around the egg. Chorion white, translucent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7C85650B6C66FF89FF0CF95FFD9FF73D" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="357" pageId="0" pageNumber="353" type="description">
<paragraph id="342036806C66FF8DFF0CF95FFB27F169" blockId="0.[166,1225,1635,1854]" pageId="0" pageNumber="353">
Chorion ridged, marked on two-thirds of surfaces. Micropylar area clearly expressed, represented by rosette and 4 rows of petalled cells (
<figureCitation id="ACA42A056C66FF8DFCD2F97FFCAAF0A9" box="[773,836,1763,1790]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[172,205,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[174,1228,201,1672]" captionTargetId="figure-5@1.[174,1228,201,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Eggs of Acronictinae: Acronicta megacephala. Scale bars: 1, 4 — 100 µm; 2, 3, 5, 6 — 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453276/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="353">fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Rosette with 13–15 cells. Walls cells elevated. Central portion of rosette with round depression. (
<figureCitation id="ACA42A056C66FF8DFC6EF89FFC16F149" box="[953,1016,1795,1822]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[172,205,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[174,1228,201,1672]" captionTargetId="figure-5@1.[174,1228,201,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Eggs of Acronictinae: Acronicta megacephala. Scale bars: 1, 4 — 100 µm; 2, 3, 5, 6 — 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453276/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="353">fig. 3</figureCitation>
). There are 30 of 73–76 longitudinal ridges radiating from cells of fourth row. Longest ridges unevenly wavy
</paragraph>
<caption id="60E066086C67FF8CFF7BF954FB98F089" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453276" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6453276" box="[172,1142,1736,1758]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453276/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="354" startId="1.[172,205,1736,1758]" targetBox="[174,1228,201,1672]" targetPageId="1">
